cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.DS

The paper discusses theories of behavioural contracts and choreographies in multiparty interactions, which are related to formal methods and software engineering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), which deals with formal reasoning and verification. The paper also discusses compliance testing and controllability theory, which are related to software testing and control theory, respectively. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions CCS/pi-calculus, which is a process calculus used for modelling concurrent systems, and asynchronous communication, which is a common feature of distributed systems. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also possible sub-categories.
